<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="R" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Redress2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Redress,</orth> vb. to set right, to remedy, to relieve from: <cit><quote>broken glass no cement can r.</quote> <bibl n="shak. pp 178" default="NO" valid="yes">Pilgr. 178</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>if it be confessed, it is not --ed,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.1.107" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 1, 107</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>each article herein --ed,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.1.170" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 1, 170</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.2.59" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 59</bibl>. <emph>with honour to r.</emph> (wrongs) <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.5.126" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 5, 126</bibl>. <cit><quote>to r. their harms,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.4.2" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C V, 4, 2</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>what you would thus violently r.</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 3.1.220" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. III, 1, 220</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>speak, strike, r.</quote> <bibl n="shak. jc 2.1.47" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. II, 1, 47</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>that Caesar must r.</quote> <bibl n="shak. jc 3.1.32" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 32</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>what I can r.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 4.3.9" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. IV, 3, 9</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>